						<summary>

						<p>Stone standing in the field called Appaṇṇi-hola.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription commences with an obeisance to Śrī-Kṛishṇa and mentions a Brāhmaṇa of Ṛik-śākhā and Āśvalāyana-sūtra, other details being lost. The characters belong to about 16th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
